papers.abstract:
The C++ Standard Template Library (STL) is the exemplar of generic&#13;
libraries. Professional C++ programs cannot miss the usage of this standard&#13;
library because it increases quality, maintainability, understandability and&#13;
eﬃcacy of the code. However, the usage of C++ STL does not guarantee&#13;
error-free code. Contrarily, incorrect application of the library may intro-&#13;
duce new types of problems. Unfortunately, there is still a large number of&#13;
properties are tested neither at compilation-time nor at run-time. It is not&#13;
surprising that in implementation of C++ programs so many STL-related&#13;
bugs are occurred.&#13;
We match patterns on abstract syntax trees (AST) with the help of predicates.&#13;
The predicates can be combined and deﬁne an embedded language.&#13;
We have developed a tool which ﬁnds the potential missuses of the STL as a&#13;
validation of our approach. The software takes advantage of the Clang ASTMatcher&#13;
technology. The tool is in-use in Ericsson. We advise new matchers&#13;
that have get into the Clang code base.&#13;
Keywords: C++ STL, generic programming, Clang, AST, static analysis,&#13;
code validation
